claim.claim-text:
1. A process cartridge detachably mountable to a main assembly of an electrophotographic image forming apparatus, comprising: 
an electrophotographic photosensitive drum; 
charging means, contacted to said electrophotographic photosensitive drum along a length of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum, for electrically charging said electrophotographic photosensitive drum by application of a bias voltage to said charging means; 
cleaning means, contacted to said electrophotographic photosensitive drum, for removing a developer remaining on said electrophotographic photosensitive drum; 
holding means for holding said cleaning means along the length of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum; and 
storing means including a storing portion for storing predetermined information and communicating means for effecting wireless communication of the predetermined information stored in said storing portion with main assembly side communicating means provided in a main assembly of said electrophotographic image forming apparatus; 
wherein said storing means is disposed in a region blinded by said holding means as seen in a direction crossing with a longitudinal direction of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum from a given contact point between said electrophotographic photosensitive drum and said charging means.

3. A process cartridge detachably mountable to a main assembly of an electrophotographic image forming apparatus, comprising: 
an electrophotographic photosensitive drum; 
charging means, contacted to said electrophotographic photosensitive drum along a length of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum, for electrically charging said electrophotographic photosensitive drum by application of a bias voltage to said charging means; and 
storing means including a storing portion for storing predetermined information and communicating means for effecting wireless communication of the predetermined information stored in said storing portion with main assembly side communicating means provided in a main assembly of said electrophotographic image forming apparatus; 
wherein said storing means is disposed closer to said electrophotographic photosensitive drum than a tangent line passing through a contact point between said electrophotographic photosensitive drum and said charging means and extending in a direction crossing with the longitudinal direction of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum.

4. A process cartridge detachably mountable to a main assembly of an electrophotographic image forming apparatus having transferring means, said process cartridge comprising: 
an electrophotographic photosensitive drum; 
developing means for developing an electrostatic latent image formed on said electrophotographic photosensitive drum with a developer; and 
storing means including a storing portion for storing predetermined information and communicating means for effecting wireless communication of the predetermined information stored in said storing portion with main assembly side communicating means provided in a main assembly of said electrophotographic image forming apparatus; 
wherein said electrophotographic photosensitive drum is contacted along a length thereof to said transferring means for receiving a bias voltage to transfer a developed image provided by said developing means onto a recording material; 
wherein said storing means is disposed closer to said electrophotographic photosensitive drum than a tangent line passing through a contact point between said electrophotographic photosensitive drum and said transferring means and extending in a direction crossing with the longitudinal direction of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum.

5. A process cartridge detachably mountable to a main assembly of an electrophotographic image forming apparatus, comprising: 
an electrophotographic photosensitive drum; 
developing means for receiving a bias voltage and contacted to said electrophotographic photosensitive drum along a length of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum to develop an electrostatic latent image formed on said electrophotographic photosensitive member with a developer; and 
storing means including a storing portion for storing predetermined information and communicating means for effecting wireless communication of the predetermined information stored in said storing portion with main assembly side communicating means provided in a main assembly of said electrophotographic image forming apparatus; 
wherein said storing means is disposed closer to said electrophotographic photosensitive drum than a tangent line passing through a contact point between said electrophotographic photosensitive drum and said developing means and extending in a direction crossing with the longitudinal direction of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum.

6. A process cartridge detachably mountable to a main assembly of an electrophotographic image forming apparatus having transferring means, said process cartridge comprising: 
an electrophotographic photosensitive drum; 
charging means, contacted to said electrophotographic photosensitive drum along a length of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum, for electrically charging said electrophotographic photosensitive drum by application of a bias voltage to said charging means; 
developing means for receiving a bias voltage and contacted to said electrophotographic photosensitive drum along a length of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum to develop an electrostatic latent image formed on said electrophotographic photosensitive member with a developer; and 
storing means including a storing portion for storing predetermined information and communicating means for effecting wireless communication of the predetermined information stored in said storing portion with main assembly side communicating means provided in a main assembly of said electrophotographic image forming apparatus; 
wherein said electrophotographic photosensitive drum is contacted along a length thereof to said transferring means for receiving a bias voltage to transfer a developed image provided by said developing means onto a recording material; 
wherein said storing means is disposed outside a phantom circle having a center on a longitudinal axis of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum and including said charging means, said developing means and said transferring means.

7. An electrophotographic image forming apparatus for forming an image on a recording material, to which a process cartridge is detachably mountable, said apparatus comprising: 
(a) main assembly side communicating means provided in a main assembly of said image forming apparatus; 
(b) mounting means for detachably mounting a process cartridge, said process cartridge including: 
an electrophotographic photosensitive drum; 
charging means, contacted to said electrophotographic photosensitive drum along a length of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum, for electrically charging said electrophotographic photosensitive drum by application of a bias voltage to said charging means; 
cleaning means, contacted to said electrophotographic photosensitive drum, for removing a developer remaining on said electrophotographic photosensitive drum; and 
storing means including a storing portion for storing predetermined information and communicating means for effecting wireless communication of the predetermined information stored in said storing portion with said main assembly side communicating means provided in a main assembly of said electrophotographic image forming apparatus; 
wherein said storing means is disposed in a region blinded by said holding means as seen in a direction crossing with a longitudinal direction of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum from a given contact point between said electrophotographic photosensitive drum and said charging means; and 

(c) feeding means for feeding the recording material.

9. An electrophotographic image forming apparatus for forming an image on a recording material, to which a process cartridge is detachably mountable, said apparatus comprising: 
(a) main assembly side communicating means provided in a main assembly of said image forming apparatus; 
(b) mounting means for detachably mounting said process cartridge, said process cartridge including: 
an electrophotographic photosensitive drum; 
charging means, contacted to said electrophotographic photosensitive drum along a length of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum, for electrically charging said electrophotographic photosensitive drum by application of a bias voltage to said charging means; and 
storing means including a storing portion for storing predetermined information and communicating means for wireless communication of the predetermined information stored in said storing portion with said main assembly side communicating means; 
wherein said storing means is disposed closer to said electrophotographic photosensitive drum than a tangent line passing through a contact point between said electrophotographic photosensitive drum and said charging means and extending in a direction crossing with the longitudinal direction of said electrophotographic photosensitive drum; and 

(c) feeding means for feeding the recording material.

